   HealthVest Standstill Accord
</HL>
<DATE>
05/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   HVT
</CO>
<LP>
   AUSTIN, Texas -- HealthVest, a real estate investment
trust, said it has complied with documentation requirements
of a standstill agreement with lenders and expects the accord
to remain in effect until Dec. 14.
   Under terms, HealthVest's lender groups have agreed to
refrain from foreclosing on about $270 million of property
that was pledged as collateral to secure about $252 million
in debt.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   During the standstill period, the trust said it will
continue efforts to restructure the debt. The lenders
involved include Chemical Banking Corp.'s Chemical Bank, the
Bank of Tokyo, a group of European banks and several U.S.
insurance companies.
</TEXT>
