<HL>
   International Brief -- Bayerische Motoren Werke AG:
   German Auto Maker's Net
   Jumped 23% During 1989
</HL>
<DATE>
05/03/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A15
</SO>
<CO>
   G.BMW
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Bayerische Motoren Werke AG, citing high customer demand
for its entire model range, said group net income in 1989
soared 23% as sales gained 8.4%.
   The West German luxury car maker said profit gained to
558.1 million marks ($332.2 million) from 454.9 million marks
a year ago, as sales grew to 26.52 billion marks from 24.47
billion marks.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   BMW said it produced 511,476 passenger cars in 1989, up
5.7% from 484,121 cars in 1988. New car registrations in the
U.S., however, fell 12% to 64,900 from 73,400.
   This is the first time the company has reported full
consolidated world-wide annual group financial data.
   Separately, BMW said group sales rose 4.1% to 9.24 billion
marks in the first four months of 1990 from 8.87 billion
marks a year earlier.
   BMW said group car output rose 5.5% to 191,749 from
181,739 in the period.
